HEADWORD: Rapier
<hw>Ra"pi*er</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧"p⟦icr⟧*⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>rapi⟦egrave⟧re</ets>, perhaps for
<ets>raspi⟦egrave⟧re</ets>, and ultimately of German origin, akin to E.
<ets>rasp</ets>, v.]</ety> <def>A straight sword, with a narrow and
finely pointed blade, used only for thrusting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Rapier fish</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
